<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="1573" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1573">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.62/43.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Hostetter</persName>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi><note n="148" xml:id="d1573fn148">Communicated to the American Chargé
                                    d’Affaires at Mexico City February 2, 1914.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Hermosillo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-01">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 1, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Department’s January 31,7 p, m. Carranza claims German Minister’s
                                charges are absurd as no such orders were ever issued. Orders have
                                been issued to respect life and property of all foreigners, all
                                nationalities included. Some foreigners have mixed in politics and
                                these may have suffered some inconvenience but none are molested who
                                remain neutral. He has asked for information and will advise as soon
                                as received.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hostetter</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>